				<p><p>Well, when you change the value of PWM to 0 in an instant, it will definitely shut the servo down, but it will happen in such a sudden fashion that it could break the servo. I am also partaking in this event as well at my school and we are also had the same problem. We even tried setting the value of PWM to 0 in the end, but it broke two of our servos due to the sudden movement. What I recommend is, which I used with my FTC robot to solve my problem is to decrease the value of the angle instead of the PWM by decreasing the servo angle, or speed, by 1.25 every second. Every second is crucial in the games so it is always helpful to use your time efficiently and as fast as possible.</p>
